{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8ec-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10516"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10516"},"text":"§ 10516.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reports","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Each State or unit of local government which receives a grant under this subchapter shall submit to the Attorney General, for each year in which funds from a grant received under this subchapter is expended, a report at such time and in such manner as the Attorney General may reasonably require which contains—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8ed-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10516/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the activities carried out under the grant and an assessment of whether such activities are meeting the needs identified in the application submitted under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s10512"},"text":"section 10512 of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8ee-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10516/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such other information as the Attorney General may require.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4ccba8ef-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/351/tI/s2406"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–351, title I, § 2406","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tXXI/s210302/c/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title XXI, § 210302(c)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2067"},"text":"108 Stat. 2067","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/189/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–189, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1435"},"text":"126 Stat. 1435","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4ccba8f0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4ccba8f1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4ccba8f2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3796kk–5"},"text":"section 3796kk–5 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4ccba8f3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/189"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–189","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (a) designation and heading “Reports to Attorney General” before “Each State” and struck out subsec. (b) which required the Attorney General to submit reports to Congress on grant amounts and activities."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
